about several opioid related resources and trainings for healthcare providers and administration.          Opioid Task Force  An interprofessional task force was developed at UIC in late 2018.          Opioid Repository  The Task Force has created a central repository highlighting opioid related projects and expertise at UIC.          Grants  Learn more about funding opportunities.           Improving Opioid Safety at UI Health      In the U.S., more people die from prescription opioid overdose than from illegal drugs like heroin, cocaine, and methamphetamine — combined. At UI Health, we are improving the safety of opioid therapy by taking steps to ensure the responsible use of opioid drugs to relieve pain and safeguard against their destructive potential. As individuals and as an organization, we share responsibility for helping resolve this epidemic. When we thoughtfully prescribe, carefully check and verify, and closely monitor opioid therapy, we ensure that we keeping are patient’s safe while providing them with the best care available.      Opioid Project and Research Highlights at UI Health           Opioid use among kidney disease patients  UIC received $2.8 million in funding from the National Institutes of Health to investigate non opioid pain management.             An opioid alternative  Physical therapy at UI Health - An opioid alternative.             Reducing deaths from opioid overdoses  Dr. Schwartz is at the forefront of research related to the opioid epidemic in Illinois.           Opioid Events of Interest       Mar  4  2020        UIC's Response to Opioid Epidemic  Wednesday, 6:00 pm - 8:00 pm                          UIC Logo         Office of  the Vice  Chancellor  for Health  Affairs         Contact   Medical Center Administration (MCA), 914 S. Wood St., Chicago, IL 60612  Phone: (312) 413-5473  vcha@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Em